          "title": "Positions from FEN",
          "code_path": "Games/Chess/Core/Private/Board.cpp",
          "line_start": 35,
          "line_end": 56,
          "note": "A small Forsyth–Edwards Notation parser — how the perft tests load standard positions (and how StartPosition is defined). Hand-rolled, per the no-libraries rule. Parses placement, side to move, castling rights, en-passant square, and the two clocks.",
          "note_comments": [],
          "code_comments": []
        },
        {
          "id": "01KV0N144QRZQKXC2P8BCH86ES",
          "title": "Perft: the correctness gate",
          "code_path": "Games/Chess/Core/Tests/ChessRulesTests.cpp",
          "line_start": 25,
          "line_end": 36,
          "note": "Perft counts the exact number of legal-move leaf nodes to a given depth. Any bug anywhere — generation, make-move, castling, EP, promotion, legality — shifts the counts. Matching long-published reference values across several tricky positions (this suite passes) is the standard proof of a correct generator.",
          "note_comments": [],
          "code_comments": []
        },
        {
          "id": "01KV0N144QRZQKXC2P8BCH86ET",
          "title": "The codec on real moves",
          "code_path": "Games/Chess/Core/Tests/ChessRulesTests.cpp",
          "line_start": 78,
          "line_end": 96,
          "note": "Ties move generation back to the wire protocol: every legal move from the start position encodes to its index and decodes back identically, and the 20 opening moves cost exactly 5 bits each. This is the slim-bytes promise, now exercised with real generated moves.",
